name: CoreAPI Connectivity_APIDesigner
description: Access API information that have been defined in the API Designer.
about:
Description

The CoreAPI Connectivity_APIDesigner API enables to access the APIs that are defined in the API Designer tool.

With this API, you can list all existing APIs within the system and fetch all information regarding a specific API.

Prerequisites: In order for the API to work, you will have to change the endpoint in the General tab.

Operations  performed

Important note: Please review the definitions and the request/response bodies for each operation. In certain definitions, you will a description next each field. If not, view the example data in the selected operation.

/List

Get the list of available APIs. Within each object in the returned array, the UUID of each item is placed. This is the same value that /Get operation requires.

In the example data, you will find the response body of this operation.

Body
Definition
Request
None
Response
List

/Get

Retrieve the API details corresponding to the UUID. In the example data, you will find the response body of this operation.

Body
Definition
Request
ID
Response
Get
